By Representative Giannino of Revere, a petition (accompanied by bill, House, No. 2849) of
Jessica Ann Giannino and Jacob R. Oliveira relative to credible service for veterans serving as
members of the State Staff. Public Service.
The Commonwealth of Massachusetts
_______________
In the One Hundred and Ninety-Fourth General Court
(2025-2026)
_______________
An Act amending credible service of the State Staff.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 Part 1 – Title IV – Chapter 32 – Section 4 is hereby amended by inserting the following
2 at the end of the 14th paragraph: "For the purpose of determining regular annual compensation
3 for retirement, a veteran, who has also served as a member of the State Staff for the previous 3
4 years, as defined in Chapter 33, Section 15, shall be entitled to provide makeup payments, for the
5 amount of wages that had been characterized as a housing or subsistence allowance for each year
6 of creditable service where such allowance was not included as part of regular annual
7 compensation contribution, of an amount equal to the ten percent of such housing or subsistence
8 allowance that was then not included in the veteran’s compensation calculation."
